THE CHAMBER IS SUPPORTED PRIMARILY THROUGH MEMBERSHIP DUES AND EVENTS AND ACTIVITIES INCOME.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE MEMBERS COMPRISE LOCAL BUSINESS OWNERS, EMPLOYEES, AND COMMUNITY ORGANIZERS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION'S MEMBERS CAN NOMINATE AND ELECT MEMBERS TO THE GOVERNING BOARD. THE BOARD MEMBERS AND COMMITTEE HEADS TYPICALLY CHANGE ANNUALLY TO ENCOURAGE PARTICIPATION AND INPUT FROM A DIVERSE GROUP OF MEMBERS OF THE COMMUNITY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: SOME DECISIONS SUCH AS PROGRAMS THAT MAY BE INSTITUTED ARE SUGGESTED AND VOTED ON BY MEMBERS OF THE ORGANIZATION AND THEN APPROVED BY THE GOVERNING BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: AUDITED FINANCIAL REPORTS ARE PREPARED ANNUALLY BY OUTSIDE CERTIFIED PUBLIC ACCOUNTANTS AND ARE REVIEWED AND APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. FORM 990 IS PREPARED BASED ON THESE APPROVED AUDITED FINANCIAL REPORTS. THE 990 IS REVIEWED AND APPROVED BY EMPLOYEES WHO ARE CHARGED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS WITH THE RESPONSIBILITY FOR THE TAX RETURN FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MEMBERS OF THE NORTH DALLAS CHAMBER OF COMMERCE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ARE COMMITTED TO OPERATING IN A MANNER CONSISTENT WITH THE CHARITABLE PURPOSES OF THE ORGANIZATION AND TO NOT ENGAGE IN ACTIVITIES THAT COULD JEOPARDIZE ITS TAX-EXEMPT STATUS. TOWARD THAT PURPOSE, THE ORGANIZATION IS CONSISTENTLY WORKING TO ENSURE THAT INTEGRITY AND FAIRNESS ARE AT THE CORE OF THEIR BUSINESS RELATIONSHIPS AND BUSINESS TRANSACTIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE SALARIES AND EMPLOYEE INCENTIVE PLANS ARE DEVELOPED AND APPROVED BY BOARD MEMBERS. THE INCENTIVE PLAN IS TO MOTIVATE AND RECOGNIZE CHAMBER LEADERSHIP'S ACHIEVEMENTS AS WELL AS INDIVIDUAL STAFF ACHIEVEMENTS. THE ACTUAL PAYMENT OF AN INCENTIVE IS AT THE DISCRETION OF THE BOARD IN CONSULTATION WITH THE PRESIDENT AND CEO BASED ON THE OVERALL FINANCIAL RESULTS FOR THE CHAMBER. THE BOARD DETERMINES IF AN INCENTIVE SHOULD BE PAID AND THE AGGREGATE AMOUNT IN ANY GIVEN YEAR. THE PRESIDENT AND CEO WILL BE RESPONSIBLE FOR THE ALLOCATION OF ANY INCENTIVE FOR STAFF. THE BOARD WILL MAKE THE INCENTIVE DETERMINATION FOR THE PRESIDENT AND CEO.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL DOCUMENTS CONCERNING THE ORGANIZATIONS ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST OR BY PERSONAL CONVERSATION WITH MEMBERS OF THE ORGANIZATION.
